.idnes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-cesko-nakazeni-jihocesky-kraj.A200312_065829_domaci_bur|title=Infected count topped 100, half of infected are in Prague, said Babis|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''96'''\n| 12 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}} \n| {{Success|Travel-related}}\n| {{flag|Italy}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| [[Liberec Region]]\n| {{Partial failure|Regional Hospital Liberec}}\n| Female\n| 59\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | The first case in [[Liberec Region]] is a 59-year-old woman who was skiing in Italy. She had symptoms and stayed home after she told her employer, she moved to hospital on 10 March. Reportedly in mild condition.<ref name=\"mar12.news.idnes\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''97'''\n| 12 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}} \n| {{Success|Travel-related}}\n| {{flag|Italy}}\n| {{n/a}}\n| [[Karlovy Vary Region]]\n| {{Success|Home isolation}}\n| Male\n| 65+\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | The first case in [[Karlovy Vary Region]] is a man over 65 years old who was skiing in Italy. Mild condition.<ref name=\"mar12.news.idnes\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''98'''\n| 12 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}} \n| {{Partial failure|Person-to-person spread}}\n| {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Prague]]\n| [[Litomy\u0161l]]\n| [[Pardubice Region]]\n| {{Partial failure|Pardubice Hospital}}\n| Female\n| 30\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | The second case in [[Pardubice Region]] is a woman from Litomy\u0161l that was infected in Prague. She works in administrative and was in contact with another case, which is why she was tested. Even though she has no symptoms, regional epidemiologist said she will be transferred to Pardubice Hospital.<ref name=\"mar12.news.idnes\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''99'''\n| 12 March 2020\n| {{Partial failure|Confirmed}} \n| {{Failure|Community spread}}\n| {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Fr\u00fddek-M\u00edstek]]\n| [[Fr\u00fddek-M\u00edstek]]\n| [[Moravian-Silesian Region]]\n| {{n/a}}\n| Female\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{flag|CZE}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n| colspan=\"10\" | A nurse from hospital in Fr\u00fddek-M\u00edstek with no travel history and no known relation to other cases.<ref name=case99>{{cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/koronavirus-v-cesku-v-cr-aktualne-novinky-frydek-mistek-moravskoslezsky-kraj_2003122301_ako|title=A nurse from Frydek-Mistek hospital has been infected. She had no travel history.|website=irozhlas.cz|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Policies to fight the contagion==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width: 100%;\"\n|+ <strong>Policy details</strong>\n|-\n! Type of Measure\n! Specific\n! Details\n! Date enacted\n! In force\n! Note\n! Authority\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=10 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Soft measures'''\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=6 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Travel restrictions''' (''before border closure'')\n| Suspension of issuing of new visas in China.\n| 30 January 2020\n| Indefinitely.\n| Visas issued prior remained valid.\n| Ministry of Foreign Affairs<ref name=visa.china.stop>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/ministerstvo-zahranici-okamzite-prestalo-cinanum-vydavat-viza-40311716|title=Ministry of Foreign Affairs stops issuing visas for Chinese citizens|website=novinky.cz|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Suspension of direct flights to/from '''China'''.\n| 8 February 2020\n| From 9 February onwards (indefinitely).\n| Ten direct flights a week, all of them cancelled.\n| Ministry of Health<ref name=china.flights.stop>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/vlada-zakaze-prime-lety-z-ciny-40312057|title=Government bans direct flights from China due to coronavirus|website=novinky.cz|access-date=3 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Suspension of direct flights to/from selected regions of '''Italy'''.\n| 2 March 2020\n| From 5 March 2020 '''until 19 March 2020'''.\n| All direct flights to/from Italian regions Emillia-Romagna, Piemont, Lombardia, Venetia suspended.\n\nAround 100,000\u2013110,000 Czechs visited Northern Italy over the previous month (mostly for skiing holidays).\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-6/PRO<ref name=\"italy flights measure\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40428&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Ochrann%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20MZ%20%C4%8CR_lety%20It%C3%A1lie.pdf |title=Allie |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Suspension of direct flights to/from '''South Korea'''.\n| 2 March 2020\n| From 5 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Revoked on 24 March 2020.'''\n| All direct flights to/from South Korea suspended.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-5/PRO<ref name=\"Iran visas\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40429&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Ochrann%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20MZ%20%C4%8CR_lety%20Korea.pdf |title=Korea data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-15/PRO (revocation)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40697&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20ochrann%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%202.%20b%C5%99ezna%202020%20k%20z%C3%A1kazu%20let%C5%AF%20z%20Korejsk%C3%A9%20republiky.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Suspension of issuing of new visas in '''Iran'''.\n| 7 March 2020\n| From 7 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Applies to all applicants requesting visas in Iran (notwithstanding nationality).\n| Ministry of Foreign Affairs<ref name=visa.iran.stop>{{cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/koronavirus-online-koronavir-cesko-nakazeni-ministr-vojtech-cina-chu-pej-wu-chan_2003070631_jgr|title=The Czech Republic has 5 new infections, total has grown to 26.|website=iRozhlas.cz|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Random medical checks at major border crossings\n| 7 March 2020\n| From 9 March 7&nbsp;am onwards (indefinitely).\n| Major border crossings (Rozvadov, Folmava, \u017delezn\u00e1 ruda, Doln\u00ed Dvo\u0159i\u0161t\u011b, Str\u00e1\u017en\u00fd, Mikulov, Hat\u011b, B\u0159eclav, C\u00ednovec, and Pomez\u00ed) manned by a combination of police, customs, and fire service personnel.\n\nDrivers provided with informational leaflets in Czech, English, German and Italian.\n\nRandom temperature checks of vehicle occupants.\n\nSimilar measures put in place at all international airports as well as in cross-border trains.\n\nPeople with symptoms can either turn back at the border or be transported by a [[Dangerous goods|HAZMAT]] ambulance for medical examination at the nearest hospital.\n\nArmy deployed on 10 March (see below).\n| Government<ref name=\"border leaflets\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/ministerstvo-zdravotnictvi-vydalo-nove-mimoradne-opatreni-tykajici-se-karanteny-_18668_4107_1.html|title=Ministerstvo zdravotnictv\u00ed vydalo nov\u00e9 mimo\u0159\u00e1dn\u00e9 opat\u0159en\u00ed t\u00fdkaj\u00edc\u00ed se karant\u00e9ny osob, kter\u00e9 se vracej\u00ed z It\u00e1lie|website=mzcr.cz}}</ref><ref name=italy.quarantine.idnes>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/karantena-koronavirus-vyjimka.A200307_115240_domaci_zaz|title=The Czech Republic has 26 infected. Mandatory quarantine also for foreigners|website=Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|language=cs |access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center;\" | Restrictions on sale of medical means\n| '''FFP3 respirators sale ban'''\n\nFFP3 respirators may be sold only to:\n* healthcare providers (''exemption revoked on 6 March'')\n* welfare providers (''exemption revoked on 6 March'')\n* Czech Republic government and its component agencies\n* resellers of FFP3 based in the Czech Republic, provided resellers will sell only to the other groups mentioned\n| 3 March 2020\n| From 4 March onwards (indefinitely)\n\n'''Revoked on 6 April 2020'''\n| The FFP3 respirators sale ban was preceded by a memo from [[Security Information Service]] to the Government, according to which Chinese embassy in Prague was conducting massive purchases of respirators available on Czech market during January and February and transferring them to China.<ref name=\"BIS report\">{{cite web|url=https://denikn.cz/324728/cina-v-cesku-skupuje-respiratory-a-rousky-varovala-babise-a-ministry-bis/|title=\u010c\u00edna v \u010cesku skupuje respir\u00e1tory a rou\u0161ky, varovala Babi\u0161e a ministry BIS|last=Prchal|first=Luk\u00e1\u0161|date=24 March 2020|website=Den\u00edk N|language=cs|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThis led to shortage of FFP3 respirators for use by healthcare providers which lasted for weeks after the ban was passed.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-8/PRO<ref name=\"ffp3 sale restriction\">[[:File:Mimo\u0159\u00e1dn\u00e9 opat\u0159en\u00ed - z\u00e1kaz v\u00fdvozu v\u0161ech respir\u00e1tor\u016f t\u0159\u00eddy FFP3 mimo \u010cR.pdf]]</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-12/PRO<ref name=\"ffp3 sale restriction no 2\">{{cite web|url=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/53/Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9_opat%C5%99en%C3%AD_-_prodej_osobn%C3%ADch_ochrann%C3%BDch_prost%C5%99edk%C5%AF_t%C5%99%C3%ADdy_FFP3.pdf |title=Prodej |publisher=upload.wikimedia.org |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15190/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40878&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Zru%C5%A1en%C3%AD%20mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%206.%203.%202020%20k%20prodeji%20OOP%20t%C5%99%C3%ADdy%20FFP3.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref> (revocation)\n|-\n| '''Hand sanitizers export ban.'''\n| 5 March 2020\n| From 5 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Ban on export of hand sanitizers listed in Annex 1, Category 1 of EU Regulation No. 528/2012 (with exemption of small amounts for personal use).\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 5503/2020-9/PRO<ref name=\"hand sanitizers restrictions\">{{cite web|url=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cf/Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9_opat%C5%99en%C3%AD_-_z%C3%A1kaz_v%C3%BDvozu_desinfekce_rukou.pdf |title=Aikaz |publisher=upload.wikimedia.org |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Ban on export of medication'''\n| 17 March 2020\n| From 17 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| 17 March \u2013 1 April 2020 \u2013 general ban on export of medication.\n\nFrom 1 April onwards \u2013 ban on export of selected medication.\n\nBan only on export of medication destined for the Czech market. Medication manufactured directly to foreign order may still be exported.\n| Government Regulation No. 104/2020 Coll. (until 1 April)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38815 |title=Sbirka |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nGovernment Regulation No. 146/2020. Coll (after 1 April)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38833 |title=Info |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Duty to report gatherings over 5,000 people.\n| Organisers must inform health authorities about all planned gatherings where they expect 5,000 or more visitors during a single day\n| 4 March 2020\n| From 4 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| \n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 9826/2020-1/HES<ref name=\"gatherings 5000\">{{cite web|url=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%